# TrailPrint3D Changelog

Version 3.09

- Added: Info Popup when Exporting manually
- Added: Automatic Version Updater (Only free version)
- Added: Minimum Road width setting
- Changed: Increased road thickness. "Unclassified" roads are now medium roads instead of small
- Changed: Adjusted scale to Mercator projection
- Fixed: Ocean cutoff for rectangular shape
- Fixed: Cache not getting deleted properly
- Fixed: Single-color Mode where elements are above a certain threshold
- Fixed: Error when Trail object is empty
- Fixed: Greenspace in Single-color Mode

Version 3.08

- Added: HTML based Progress Bar that does not Freeze
- Changed: Roads and buildings are no longer clipping into the Map
- Changed: Improved reliability of the Single-color-mode
- Removed: Rescale Elevation (Conflicting with Single-color-mode, Unnecessary since caching)
- Removed: Extrude Terrain (Conflicting with Single-color-mode, Unnecessary since caching)

Version 3.05

- Fixed missing duration for text shapes {duration}
- Fixed crash when using 2 identical icons for text shapes

Version 3.04

- Added Greenspace element (Parks, grass, gardens inside cities)
- Added Another Single-color-mode Algorithm for elements
- Improved existing SCM algorithm for elements. Bevel is now gone and vertice count reduced massively -> Better performance
- Improved River generation. Rivers thickness can now be modified
- Fixed: Many buidlings were missing
- Fixed: Negative islands (Cutouts in elements) were creating floating objects when combining single-color-mode with a Text based shape
- Fixed: Some weird behaviour from the Single-color-mode on the outer rim
- Fixed: elements with "Separate objects" selected are now 1mm thick instead of having a flat bottom
- Fixed: Wrong position of Roads and buiildings in 3mf export
- Fixed: Coloring Mountains behaved weirdly if it had multiple materials applied

Version 3.0

- Completely Restructured the Addon Code
- optimized Coloring Mountains for less color switches (Outside walls were always staying green before, now getting colored at treshold)
- Sliding/Jigzaw puzzles, Holders, connectors are now part of the Addon (Special category of the Advanced Tab)
- Sliding/Jigzaw puzzles are generated with just one click
- Sliding/Jigzaw puzzles are now compatible with Multi-generation
- More flexibility for Text Based Shapes
- Added Printable Icons to the Text Based Shapes
- Added SVG Import
- Added Custom Text Import
- Completely reworked the "Merge with Map" Function. Now 4 diffrent Options
  - Paint on Map
  - Project but keep as separate Object
  - Single-color-mode
  - Negative
- Added Roads
- Elements wont Generate if the Map area is too big to prevent Crashes (individual limit for each element)
- Objects are now properly getting cleared up when using x and y TerrainOffset
- Variable Aspect ratio for the Ellipse Shape
- Variable Width/Height for the Rectangle Shape (Previous only Squares possible)
- Replaced the Console Window with a Progress Bar
- Restructured the UI
- New Export format: .3mf (by downloading the 3mf Addon by Clonephaze)
- You can set a default Export older in the Addon preferences
- Oceans Beta
- Added Stone Elements (Mainly for mountain tips)
- Added Farmland elements
- Added Bevel setting to Plate Shapes (requested by @BH)
- Added Opentopography as another optional API for the elevation (thanks to @FLG)
- GPX files from more sources are now compatible
- option to disable auto 3mf Exports or automated exports
- Chinese and German Translation
